<TeXmacs|2.1.4>

<style|generic>

<\body>
  <doc-data|<doc-title|An example on using the <TeXmacs> plugin>>

  We study the first quotation from Matthew. When starting the
  <with|font-series|bold|bibref> plugin, this is what we can see (it is
  assumed that <with|font-series|bold|bibref> is compiled from source and it
  detects all SWORD Bible modules being installed):\ 

  <\session|bibref|default>
    <\output>
      <\errput>
        This is bibref 2026-01-13 (database version 2025-12-07), nice to meet
        you.

        Available Bible editions: ABPGRK, ASV, Antoniades, Byz, Elzevir,
        GerNeUe, GerSch, HunRUF, HunUj, ISV, KJV, LXX, MorphGNT, Nestle1904,
        OxfordTR, SBLGNT, StatResGNT, StatResGNT-1.3, StatResGNT-1.4, TNT,
        TR, Tisch, WHNU, f35.

        Done loading books of LXX (cached).

        Done loading books of SBLGNT (cached).

        Done loading books of StatResGNT (cached).
      </errput>
    </output>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      Statement Matthew-1,23 connects

      \ StatResGNT Matthew 1:23 1:23-34 (1926-1998, length 73) with

      \ LXX Isaiah 7:14+35 7:14 (14234-14304, length 71) based on

      \ \ introduction 1:22 1:22 (1860-1925, length 66) a-z form
      toytodeolongegoneninaplhrvuhtorhuenypokyrioydiatoyprofhtoylegontos that

      \ \ \ declares a quotation with '\<tau\>\<omicron\>
      \<rho\>\<eta\>\<theta\>\<varepsilon\>\<nu\>
      \<upsilon\>\<pi\>\<omicron\> \<kappa\>\<upsilon\>\<rho\>\<iota\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>
      ... \<lambda\>\<varepsilon\>\<gamma\>\<omicron\>\<nu\>\<tau\>\<omicron\>\<varsigma\>'
      also

      \ \ \ identifies the source with '\<delta\>\<iota\>\<alpha\>
      \<tau\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\> \<pi\>\<rho\>\<omicron\>\<varphi\>\<eta\>\<tau\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>'
      moreover

      \ \ fragment 1:23 1:23-34 (1926-1998, length 73) a-z form
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikalesoysintoonomaaytoyemmanoyhl

      \ \ \ matches LXX Isaiah 7:14+35 7:14 (14234-14304, length 71) a-z form
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikaleseistoonomaaytoyemmanoyhl

      \ \ \ \ unique in Old Testament

      \ \ \ \ differing by 8.33%

      \ \ providing an overall cover of 100.00%.
    <|unfolded-io>
      1,88: info: consistent length: 1998-1926+1==73 I1

      1,88: info: `lookup1 StatResGNT Matthew 1:23 1:23-34` =
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikalesoys-intoonomaaytoyemmanoyhl
      I2

      1,88: info: `raw StatResGNT Matthew 1926 73` =
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikalesoys-intoonomaaytoyemmanoyhl
      I3

      1,88: info: results of lookup and raw match I4

      1,143: info: consistent length: 14304-14234+1==71 I1

      1,143: info: `lookup1 LXX Isaiah 7:14+35 7:14` =
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikaleseis-toonomaaytoyemmanoyhl
      I2

      1,143: info: `raw LXX Isaiah 14234 71` =
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikaleseis-toonomaaytoyemmanoyhl
      I3

      1,143: info: results of lookup and raw match I4

      1,200: info: consistent length: 1925-1860+1==66 I1

      1,446: info: `lookup1 StatResGNT Matthew 1:22 1:22` =
      toytodeolongegoneninaplhrvuhtorhuenypokyrioydiatoy-profhtoylegontos I2

      1,446: info: introduction 1:22 1:22 matches to a-z form
      toytodeolongegoneninaplhrvuhtorhuenypokyrioydiatoy-profhtoylegontos I5

      1,446: info: `raw StatResGNT Matthew 1860 66` =
      toytodeolongegoneninaplhrvuhtorhuenypokyrioydiatoy-profhtoylegontos I3

      1,446: info: results of lookup and raw match I4

      1,446: info: substring torhuenypokyrioy found in introduction I6

      1,446: info: substring legontos found in introduction I6

      1,446: info: substring diatoyprofhtoy found in introduction I6

      1,493: info: consistent length: 1998-1926+1==73 I1

      1,636: info: consistent length: 14304-14234+1==71 I1

      1,636: info: `lookup1 LXX Isaiah 7:14+35 7:14` =
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikaleseis-toonomaaytoyemmanoyhl
      I2

      1,636: info: `raw LXX Isaiah 14234 71` =
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikaleseis-toonomaaytoyemmanoyhl
      I3

      1,636: info: results of lookup and raw match I4

      1,768: info: `lookup1 StatResGNT Matthew 1:23 1:23-34` =
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikalesoys-intoonomaaytoyemmanoyhl
      I2

      1,768: info: NT fragment 1:23 1:23-34 matches to a-z form I7

      1,768: info: `raw StatResGNT Matthew 1926 73` =
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikalesoys-intoonomaaytoyemmanoyhl
      I3

      1,768: info: results of lookup and raw match I4

      1,768: info: `lookup1 LXX Isaiah 7:14+35 7:14` =
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikaleseis-toonomaaytoyemmanoyhl
      I2

      1,768: info: OT fragment LXX Isaiah 7:14+35 7:14 matches to a-z form I8

      1,768: info: fragments differ by 8.33% I9

      1,768: info: checking if OT passage is unique in OT: yes I11

      1,808: info: cover 100.00% is correct I12

      1,808: info: NT overlap check done I13

      1,808: info: NT headline interval check done I14

      1,808: info: OT headline 1 LXX Isaiah has at least one corresponding
      fragment I15

      1,808: info: OT headline interval 1 check done I16

      1,808: info: OT interval check for OT headline 1 done I17

      1,808: info: all OT intervals belong to an OT headline I18

      Finished
    </unfolded-io>
  </session>

  We immediately copied an example statement and pressed <kbd|Enter>. Now, we
  want to visualize the input since the parsing was successful.

  <\session|bibref|default>
    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      diagram ps
    <|unfolded-io>
      Diagram output is set to ps.
    </unfolded-io>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      Statement Matthew-1,23 connects

      \ StatResGNT Matthew 1:23 1:23-34 (1926-1998, length 73) with

      \ LXX Isaiah 7:14+35 7:14 (14234-14304, length 71) based on

      \ \ introduction 1:22 1:22 (1860-1925, length 66) a-z form
      toytodeolongegoneninaplhrvuhtorhuenypokyrioydiatoyprofhtoylegontos that

      \ \ \ declares a quotation with '\<tau\>\<omicron\>
      \<rho\>\<eta\>\<theta\>\<varepsilon\>\<nu\>
      \<upsilon\>\<pi\>\<omicron\> \<kappa\>\<upsilon\>\<rho\>\<iota\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>
      ... \<lambda\>\<varepsilon\>\<gamma\>\<omicron\>\<nu\>\<tau\>\<omicron\>\<varsigma\>'
      also

      \ \ \ identifies the source with '\<delta\>\<iota\>\<alpha\>
      \<tau\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\> \<pi\>\<rho\>\<omicron\>\<varphi\>\<eta\>\<tau\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>'
      moreover

      \ \ fragment 1:23 1:23-34 (1926-1998, length 73) a-z form
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikalesoysintoonomaaytoyemmanoyhl

      \ \ \ matches LXX Isaiah 7:14+35 7:14 (14234-14304, length 71) a-z form
      idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikaleseistoonomaaytoyemmanoyhl

      \ \ \ \ unique in Old Testament

      \ \ \ \ differing by 8.33%

      \ \ providing an overall cover of 100.00%.
    <|unfolded-io>
      <image|<tuple|<#>|ps>|80%|||>
    </unfolded-io>
  </session>

  To leave the <with|font-series|bold|bibref> session, one needs to press
  <kbd|Ctrl-D> twice.

  Since there are multiple SWORD modules installed, we can try retreiving
  various translations of the corresponding passages. Note that the Greek
  texts are colored:

  <\session|bibref|default>
    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      lookup LXX Isaiah 7:14
    <|unfolded-io>
      <assign|color|orange>\<delta\>\<iota\>\<alpha\>
      \<tau\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>\<tau\>\<omicron\>
      \<delta\>\<omega\>\<sigma\>\<varepsilon\>\<iota\>
      \<kappa\>\<upsilon\>\<rho\>\<iota\>\<omicron\>\<varsigma\>
      \<alpha\>\<upsilon\>\<tau\>\<omicron\>\<varsigma\>
      \<upsilon\>\<mu\>\<iota\>\<nu\> \<sigma\>\<eta\>\<mu\>\<varepsilon\>\<iota\>\<omicron\>\<nu\>
      \<iota\>\<delta\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\> \<eta\>
      \<pi\>\<alpha\>\<rho\>\<theta\>\<varepsilon\>\<nu\>\<omicron\>\<varsigma\>
      \<varepsilon\>\<nu\> \<gamma\>\<alpha\>\<sigma\>\<tau\>\<rho\>\<iota\>
      \<varepsilon\>\<xi\>\<varepsilon\>\<iota\> \<kappa\>\<alpha\>\<iota\>
      \<tau\>\<varepsilon\>\<xi\>\<varepsilon\>\<tau\>\<alpha\>\<iota\>
      \<upsilon\>\<iota\>\<omicron\>\<nu\> \<kappa\>\<alpha\>\<iota\>
      \<kappa\>\<alpha\>\<lambda\>\<varepsilon\>\<sigma\>\<varepsilon\>\<iota\>\<varsigma\>
      \<tau\>\<omicron\> \<omicron\>\<nu\>\<omicron\>\<mu\>\<alpha\>
      \<alpha\>\<upsilon\>\<tau\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>
      \<Epsilon\>\<mu\>\<mu\>\<alpha\>\<nu\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>\<eta\>\<lambda\><assign|color|black>
    </unfolded-io>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      lookup StatResGNT Matthew 1:23
    <|unfolded-io>
      <assign|color|blue>\P\<Iota\>\<delta\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>, \<eta\>
      \<pi\>\<alpha\>\<rho\>\<theta\>\<varepsilon\>\<nu\>\<omicron\>\<varsigma\>
      \<varepsilon\>\<nu\> \<gamma\>\<alpha\>\<sigma\>\<tau\>\<rho\>\<iota\>
      \<varepsilon\>\<xi\>\<varepsilon\>\<iota\> \<kappa\>\<alpha\>\<iota\>
      \<tau\>\<varepsilon\>\<xi\>\<varepsilon\>\<tau\>\<alpha\>\<iota\>
      \<upsilon\>\<iota\>\<omicron\>\<nu\>, \<kappa\>\<alpha\>\<iota\>
      \<kappa\>\<alpha\>\<lambda\>\<varepsilon\>\<sigma\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>\<sigma\>\<iota\>\<nu\>
      \<tau\>\<omicron\> \<omicron\>\<nu\>\<omicron\>\<mu\>\<alpha\>
      \<alpha\>\<upsilon\>\<tau\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>
      \<Epsilon\>\<mu\>\<mu\>\<alpha\>\<nu\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>\<eta\>\<lambda\>\Q,
      \<omicron\> \<varepsilon\>\<sigma\>\<tau\>\<iota\>\<nu\>
      \<mu\>\<varepsilon\>\<theta\>\<varepsilon\>\<rho\>\<mu\>\<eta\>\<nu\>\<varepsilon\>\<upsilon\>\<omicron\>\<mu\>\<varepsilon\>\<nu\>\<omicron\>\<nu\>,
      \P\<Mu\>\<varepsilon\>\<theta\>\<#2BC\> \<eta\>\<mu\>\<omega\>\<nu\>
      \<omicron\> \<Theta\>\<Epsilon\>\<Omicron\>\<Sigma\>\Q.<assign|color|black>
    </unfolded-io>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      lookup SBLGNT Matthew 1:23
    <|unfolded-io>
      <assign|color|blue>\<Iota\>\<delta\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\> \<eta\>
      \<pi\>\<alpha\>\<rho\>\<theta\>\<varepsilon\>\<nu\>\<omicron\>\<varsigma\>
      \<varepsilon\>\<nu\> \<gamma\>\<alpha\>\<sigma\>\<tau\>\<rho\>\<iota\>
      \<varepsilon\>\<xi\>\<varepsilon\>\<iota\> \<kappa\>\<alpha\>\<iota\>
      \<tau\>\<varepsilon\>\<xi\>\<varepsilon\>\<tau\>\<alpha\>\<iota\>
      \<upsilon\>\<iota\>\<omicron\>\<nu\>, \<kappa\>\<alpha\>\<iota\>
      \<kappa\>\<alpha\>\<lambda\>\<varepsilon\>\<sigma\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>\<sigma\>\<iota\>\<nu\>
      \<tau\>\<omicron\> \<omicron\>\<nu\>\<omicron\>\<mu\>\<alpha\>
      \<alpha\>\<upsilon\>\<tau\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>
      \<Epsilon\>\<mu\>\<mu\>\<alpha\>\<nu\>\<omicron\>\<upsilon\>\<eta\>\<lambda\>\<centerdot\>
      \<omicron\> \<varepsilon\>\<sigma\>\<tau\>\<iota\>\<nu\>
      \<mu\>\<varepsilon\>\<theta\>\<varepsilon\>\<rho\>\<mu\>\<eta\>\<nu\>\<varepsilon\>\<upsilon\>\<omicron\>\<mu\>\<varepsilon\>\<nu\>\<omicron\>\<nu\>
      \<Mu\>\<varepsilon\>\<theta\>\<#2BC\> \<eta\>\<mu\>\<omega\>\<nu\>
      \<omicron\> \<theta\>\<varepsilon\>\<omicron\>\<varsigma\>.<assign|color|black>
    </unfolded-io>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      lookup KJV Isaiah 7:14
    <|unfolded-io>
      Therefore the Lord himself shall give you a sign; Behold, a virgin
      shall conceive, and bear a son, and shall call his name Immanuel.
    </unfolded-io>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      lookup KJV Matthew 1:23
    <|unfolded-io>
      Behold, a virgin shall be with child, and shall bring forth a son, and
      they shall call his name Emmanuel, which being interpreted is, God with
      us.
    </unfolded-io>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      lookup GerNeUe Isaiah 7:14
    <|unfolded-io>
      Deshalb wird euch der Herr selbst ein Zeichen geben. Seht, die
      \Nunberührte\O junge Frau wird schwanger werden und einen Sohn zur Welt
      bringen, den sie Immanuël, Gott-mit-uns, nennt.
    </unfolded-io>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      lookup GerNeUe Matthew 1:23
    <|unfolded-io>
      'Seht, das unberührte Mädchen wird schwanger sein und einen Sohn zur
      Welt bringen, den man Immanuël nennen wird.'" Immanuël bedeutet: Gott
      ist mit uns.
    </unfolded-io>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      lookup HunRUF Isaiah 7:14
    <|unfolded-io>
      Ezért maga az Úr fog jelet adni nektek: Íme, egy fiatal n®, aki most
      várandós, fiút fog szülni, és Immánuélnak nevezi majd el.\ 
    </unfolded-io>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      lookup HunRUF Matthew 1:23
    <|unfolded-io>
      \RÍme, a sz¶z fogan méhében, és fiút szül, és Immánuélnak nevezik
      majd\Q \U ami azt jelenti: Velünk az Isten.\ 
    </unfolded-io>
  </session>

  It is possible to retrieve shorter or longer passages and display them
  nicely in the <TeXmacs> document:

  <\session|bibref|default>
    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      lookup1 LXX Isaiah 7:14
    <|unfolded-io>
      Stored internally as diatoytodvseikyriosaytosyminshmeionidoyhparuenosen-gastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikaleseistoonomaaytoyemm-anoyhl.
    </unfolded-io>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      lookup2 StatResGNT Matthew 1:23
    <|unfolded-io>
      Stored internally as idoyhparuenosengastriejeikaitejetaiyionkaikalesoys-intoonomaaytoyemmanoyhloestinmeuermhneyomenonmeuhm-vnoueos.
    </unfolded-io>

    <\unfolded-io>
      \<gtr\>\ 
    <|unfolded-io>
      jaccard12
    <|unfolded-io>
      Jaccard distance is 0.311321.
    </unfolded-io>
  </session>

  The outputs have been auto-hyphenated. Of course, the Jaccard distance here
  is greater than in the statement, because we compared full verses for this
  time.

  All the inputs above have been typed by using <kbd|Tab> completion.
</body>

<\initial>
  <\collection>
    <associate|page-medium|paper>
  </collection>
</initial>